《'''纽约灾星'''》（{{lang-en|'''''The Jinx: The Life and Deaths of Robert Durst'''''}}），是美國一部[[纪录片|纪录片]]，2015年在[[HBO|HBO]]播出，片中敘述紐約的地產商繼承人[[罗伯特·德斯特|罗伯特·德斯特]]（{{lang|en|Robert Durst}}）被指控謀殺罪，<ref name=Li>{{cite news|last1=Li|first1=David K.|title=HBO to air documentary on cross-dressing killer Robert Durst|journal=New York Post|date=December 2, 2014|url=http://nypost.com/2014/12/02/hbo-to-air-documentary-on-cross-dressing-killer-robert-durst/|accessdate=February 15, 2015|archive-date=2019-10-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191017101454/https://nypost.com/2014/12/02/hbo-to-air-documentary-on-cross-dressing-killer-robert-durst/|dead-url=no}}</ref>由{{link-en|安德魯·傑里克|Andrew Jarecki}}、{{link-en|Marc Smerling|Marc Smerling}}和Zachary Stuart-Pontier编剧<ref>{{cite news| first =Mike| last =Hale| title =‘The Jinx,’ 6-Part HBO Documentary on Robert Durst| quote =| newspaper =[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]| date =February 6, 2015| url =http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/07/arts/the-jinx-6-part-hbo-documentary-on-robert-durst.html| accessdate =March 9, 2015| archive-date =2021-03-08| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20210308124340/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/07/arts/the-jinx-6-part-hbo-documentary-on-robert-durst.html| dead-url =no}}</ref>。傑里克曾執导2010年电影《[[全為愛|全為愛]]》（{{lang|en|''All Good Things''}}），其灵感源于罗伯特·德斯特。<ref>{{cite news| first =Jim| last =Dwyer| title =Douglas Durst, in Rare Move, Speaks About Robert Durst Ahead of HBO Documentary| quote =Mr. Durst said he refused many times to be interviewed for the documentary because the same filmmakers [http://www.nytimes.com/2010/11/28/movies/28durst.html?pagewanted=all had previously made a feature film based on the Dursts,] “All Good Things,” which he believed distorted the truth, and would not give him assurances that the HBO series would not be twisted by his brother’s fabrications.| newspaper =[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]| date =January 1, 2015| url =http://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/02/nyregion/series-on-troubled-scion-of-durst-real-estate-family-has-critic-his-brother.html| accessdate =March 9, 2015| archive-date =2021-03-08| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20210308181134/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/02/nyregion/series-on-troubled-scion-of-durst-real-estate-family-has-critic-his-brother.html| dead-url =no}}</ref>

罗伯特·德斯特自称钦佩《所有美好的东西》并与傑里克通电话，提供记者采访（谈话记录被纳入纪录片）。在一年中，德斯特与傑里克座谈20多个小时，在此之前他从未与新闻媒体合作過。

该纪录片广泛播放后，在记录片结局播放的前一天，德斯特因一级谋杀罪而被捕。<ref name="NYT arrest">{{cite news| first =Caroline| last =Bankoff| title =Robert Durst Arrested for Murder| quote =| newspaper =[[New_York_Magazine|New York Magazine]]| date =March 15, 2015| url =http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2015/03/robert-durst-arrested-in-new-orleans.html| accessdate =March 15, 2015| archive-date =2018-06-12| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143215/http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2015/03/robert-durst-arrested-in-new-orleans.html| dead-url =no}}</ref>

